    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>coriander </strong>(reserve a little for garnish), <strong>green chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>trimmed spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and<strong> pepper halves</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Then add the<strong> toasted seeds</strong> and tear in the <strong>crispy seeded tortillas</strong> (careful, these may be hot!)</p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>water</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> then blitz until you have a rough paste</p><p>Tip: The seeds and tortilla act as a natural sauce thickener!</p>",
